1
00:00:01,562 --> 00:00:03,036
Previously on Riverdale...

2
00:00:04,140 --> 00:00:06,527
He calls himself the Black Hood.

3
00:00:06,530 --> 00:00:09,031
It's like the angel of
death had come to Riverdale.

4
00:00:10,001 --> 00:00:11,333
A family of four was murdered.

5
00:00:12,736 --> 00:00:14,406
There was a third child.

6
00:00:14,409 --> 00:00:16,338
Do you know who killed your family?

7
00:00:16,341 --> 00:00:18,460
A preacher, passing through town.

8
00:00:18,463 --> 00:00:19,815
A group of men killed him.

9
00:00:19,818 --> 00:00:21,183
Justice had been served.

10
00:00:22,255 --> 00:00:24,146
I know all about the Snake Charmer.

11
00:00:24,149 --> 00:00:25,814
If you cross the stink,

12
00:00:25,817 --> 00:00:28,882
I will make sure that video goes
straight to the Sheriff's office.

13
00:00:28,885 --> 00:00:30,251
I love you, Ronnie.

14
00:00:31,054 --> 00:00:33,491
Archie, whatever
deep-seated issues I have,

15
00:00:33,494 --> 00:00:35,351
I can't let myself go there with you.

16
00:00:35,354 --> 00:00:37,828
How many times are we
gonna push each other away?

17
00:00:50,069 --> 00:00:52,169
Used to be, in ye olden days,

18
00:00:52,172 --> 00:00:54,342
every December, a Lord of Misrule

19
00:00:54,344 --> 00:00:56,478
presided over the winter holidays,

20
00:00:56,481 --> 00:00:59,578
called back then, the Feast of Fools.

21
00:00:59,581 --> 00:01:01,790
What do you say, Pop? Is it okay?

22
00:01:01,793 --> 00:01:03,679
The best tree yet.

23
00:01:03,682 --> 00:01:05,460
Thanks, Archie, thanks, Fred.

24
00:01:05,463 --> 00:01:06,809
Oh, no. Thank you, Pop,

25
00:01:06,812 --> 00:01:09,585
for letting us set up shop
right in front of your diner.

26
00:01:13,414 --> 00:01:15,214
You guys gonna stay in town for break?

27
00:01:15,217 --> 00:01:17,390
Yeah. We were gonna visit my mom,

28
00:01:17,393 --> 00:01:19,609
but she booked a single's cruise so...

29
00:01:19,612 --> 00:01:21,336
How are you and Veronica?

30
00:01:22,439 --> 00:01:24,004
We've been better.

31
00:01:24,007 --> 00:01:25,773
If it's any consolation,

32
00:01:25,776 --> 00:01:28,082
Betty and I aren't in the
greatest of places, either.

33
00:01:28,085 --> 00:01:29,876
Jughead, you want a Christmas
tree, you and your dad?

34
00:01:29,878 --> 00:01:30,661
On the house.

35
00:01:30,664 --> 00:01:32,859
It'll have to be a small one, Mr. A.

36
00:01:34,196 --> 00:01:36,096
So, I'll see you at
Kevin's Secret Santa thing?

37
00:01:36,099 --> 00:01:38,820
Yeah. Because that
sounds like a great idea.

38
00:01:41,347 --> 00:01:43,406
So Christmas was happening,

39
00:01:44,528 --> 00:01:47,221
even though this year's Lord of Misrule

40
00:01:47,224 --> 00:01:49,679
was none other than the Black Hood.

41
00:01:53,537 --> 00:01:54,803
Betty.

42
00:01:54,806 --> 00:01:56,794
- Wake up, it's time.
- Polly.

43
00:01:56,797 --> 00:01:58,872
- He's here, he's waiting for us.
- What? Who?

44
00:01:58,875 --> 00:02:01,408
You know who. Come on.

45
00:02:06,883 --> 00:02:08,531
Merry Christmas.

46
00:02:08,534 --> 00:02:10,695
Hey, Merry Christmas.

47
00:02:12,573 --> 00:02:14,606
- Betty.
- Betty, Merry Christmas.

48
00:02:15,492 --> 00:02:18,459
- Okay.
- All right, honey, I told you like...

49
00:02:18,462 --> 00:02:19,527
Santa?

50
00:02:44,789 --> 00:02:47,709
- Where's Jason's stocking?
- I couldn't find it.

51
00:02:47,712 --> 00:02:51,251
And anyway, there's
nothing to put in it.

52
00:02:51,254 --> 00:02:54,590
And what, pray tell, is this?

53
00:02:56,045 --> 00:02:59,413
It's going to be a Hard Candy
Christmas this year, Cheryl.

54
00:02:59,416 --> 00:03:02,237
Time to face facts. We have no money.

55
00:03:03,976 --> 00:03:06,977
Dad, what is that? A
letter from the Black Hood?

56
00:03:07,899 --> 00:03:09,365
No, it's worse.

57
00:03:09,368 --> 00:03:12,798
Riverdale General. My hospital bill.

58
00:03:12,801 --> 00:03:13,942
How much is it for?

59
00:03:15,171 --> 00:03:17,672
- Eighty-six thousand.
- What, dollars?

60
00:03:17,675 --> 00:03:20,535
That can't be right, can it?
Or doesn't your insurance...

61
00:03:20,538 --> 00:03:23,773
They probably made a mistake.
I'll call them tomorrow.

62
00:03:25,119 --> 00:03:28,387
Kevin's Secret Santa had
a strict $20 limit, V.

63
00:03:28,390 --> 00:03:30,114
Kevin needs to relax.

64
00:03:30,117 --> 00:03:33,590
Also, these aren't just
for Secret Santa, obvi.

65
00:03:33,593 --> 00:03:35,659
I got an Hermes scarf for my mom,

66
00:03:35,662 --> 00:03:39,684
a leather passport case for my
dad, now that he can travel again,

67
00:03:39,687 --> 00:03:42,491
and a little something for my best girl.

68
00:03:43,427 --> 00:03:47,129
And a bauble for Archie.

69
00:03:47,132 --> 00:03:49,332
Because you're getting back together?

70
00:03:49,335 --> 00:03:51,466
Because it was purchased pre-breakup.

71
00:03:51,469 --> 00:03:53,869
And haven't you heard?
We're still friends.

72
00:03:53,871 --> 00:03:55,103
Oh, yeah.

73
00:03:55,106 --> 00:03:56,605
Isn't everyone?

74
00:03:58,942 --> 00:04:01,677
I was thinking about our Penny problem.

75
00:04:01,679 --> 00:04:03,660
My problem, not ours.

76
00:04:03,663 --> 00:04:07,129
Well, I am the one she has
on camera delivering drugs.

77
00:04:07,132 --> 00:04:09,818
How I deal with Peabody
is not your concern.

78
00:04:09,821 --> 00:04:11,153
I'm handling it.

79
00:04:11,156 --> 00:04:13,622
By pimping the Serpents
out as drug runners?

80
00:04:13,624 --> 00:04:14,856
Boy!

81
00:04:18,595 --> 00:04:19,661
Toss them in the corner.

82
00:04:19,663 --> 00:04:21,029
Hey, what's in the bags, Tall Boy?

83
00:04:21,031 --> 00:04:22,698
Hey, what did I just say?

84
00:04:22,701 --> 00:04:25,274
Mind your damn business
and get to school.

85
00:04:31,250 --> 00:04:32,816
Veronica, it's your turn.

86
00:04:35,145 --> 00:04:36,345
Hmm.

87
00:04:38,415 --> 00:04:42,117
Oh. A gift certificate
for a couples' massage.

88
00:04:43,911 --> 00:04:45,143
Thanks, Josie.

89
00:04:45,146 --> 00:04:48,190
You can go with Betty, or your mom...

90
00:04:48,192 --> 00:04:50,025
Or I can go with your mom, if you want.

91
00:04:50,027 --> 00:04:52,574
Oh, dear God, can we please
get this torture over with?

92
00:04:52,577 --> 00:04:54,981
Betty, you're next and mercifully last.

93
00:04:54,984 --> 00:04:58,910
Well, I think I know who picked my
name based on these wrapping skills.

94
00:05:03,741 --> 00:05:04,940
Archie...

95
00:05:04,943 --> 00:05:07,723
My dad and I were cleaning
out the garage and I found it.

96
00:05:08,781 --> 00:05:10,543
Swiss Family Robinson?

97
00:05:10,546 --> 00:05:14,080
Yeah, It's this old read-a-long record

98
00:05:14,083 --> 00:05:16,550
we used to listen to
when we were, like, five.

99
00:05:16,553 --> 00:05:17,819
Oh, my God.

100
00:05:17,822 --> 00:05:19,921
I love it, Arch. Thank you.

101
00:05:19,923 --> 00:05:21,757
Hey, Merry Christmas.

102
00:05:21,759 --> 00:05:23,392
- Moose.
- Hi.

103
00:05:27,399 --> 00:05:28,817
Why are you rushing off?

104
00:05:30,087 --> 00:05:31,520
Look, Betty,

105
00:05:32,269 --> 00:05:33,635
I don't wanna be that guy,

106
00:05:33,638 --> 00:05:35,036
but I see Moose,

107
00:05:35,038 --> 00:05:36,304
all I think about is the Black Hood

108
00:05:36,306 --> 00:05:39,007
and the pain he's caused
to the people I care about,

109
00:05:39,010 --> 00:05:40,475
including you.

110
00:05:40,477 --> 00:05:41,510
I know.

111
00:05:41,513 --> 00:05:43,311
And the fact that he's still out there

112
00:05:43,313 --> 00:05:45,046
is giving me anxiety nightmares,

113
00:05:45,049 --> 00:05:46,348
making me paranoid.

114
00:05:46,351 --> 00:05:49,885
Like, everywhere I look, all I see is...

115
00:05:50,910 --> 00:05:51,975
What?

116
00:05:51,978 --> 00:05:53,378
All you see is what?

117
00:05:57,127 --> 00:05:58,760
Excuse me. Who are you?

118
00:05:59,839 --> 00:06:01,005
You mean, my name?

119
00:06:03,018 --> 00:06:04,885
Uh, where's Mr. Svenson?

120
00:06:04,895 --> 00:06:08,426
No idea. He's been out a few days,

121
00:06:08,429 --> 00:06:10,138
they just called me in.

122
00:06:17,147 --> 00:06:20,115
Arch, you and Veronica
confronted Mr. Svenson

123
00:06:20,117 --> 00:06:21,814
about his connection to the Black Hood.

124
00:06:21,817 --> 00:06:23,051
And now he's not here.

125
00:06:24,795 --> 00:06:27,025
What if something happened to him?

126
00:06:27,028 --> 00:06:29,981
Betty, we found out
Mr. Svenson's secret...

127
00:06:29,984 --> 00:06:32,207
What if we led the
Black Hood right to him?

128
00:06:32,210 --> 00:06:33,942
What if we got him killed?

