He's been out all week with a cold.

132
00:06:46,950 --> 00:06:49,885
Sounded terrible on the phone.

133
00:06:49,888 --> 00:06:53,643
So, I dropped off some chicken
soup at his house a few days back.

134
00:06:53,646 --> 00:06:54,961
You saw him?

135
00:06:54,963 --> 00:06:56,596
I left it at his door.

136
00:06:57,306 --> 00:06:58,572
But between us,

137
00:06:58,575 --> 00:07:01,971
he often gets this way
during the holidays.

138
00:07:01,974 --> 00:07:03,702
You know, depressed.

139
00:07:03,705 --> 00:07:04,971
No family.

140
00:07:07,776 --> 00:07:09,008
Thank you.

141
00:07:13,581 --> 00:07:14,614
Hey.

142
00:07:14,617 --> 00:07:18,217
I... stayed behind

143
00:07:18,219 --> 00:07:20,820
because Merry Christmas.

144
00:07:22,624 --> 00:07:23,990
Thank you.

145
00:07:26,040 --> 00:07:27,273
I'm kinda sorry

146
00:07:28,396 --> 00:07:30,997
for how it all went down between us.

147
00:07:31,697 --> 00:07:35,802
The Serpents, my dad and I
specifically are in a precarious place.

148
00:07:35,804 --> 00:07:37,036
I...

149
00:07:37,039 --> 00:07:39,205
I just don't want you
in those crosshairs.

150
00:07:39,207 --> 00:07:41,074
That's not your decision
to make, Jughead.

151
00:07:42,844 --> 00:07:46,012
Even if you think it's to
protect me, it's my choice,

152
00:07:46,015 --> 00:07:47,705
what I risk and for whom.

153
00:07:47,708 --> 00:07:48,908
I know.

154
00:07:51,536 --> 00:07:53,803
I should go. Check on my dad.

155
00:07:54,522 --> 00:07:55,722
Jug.

156
00:07:59,070 --> 00:08:00,736
I got you something, too.

157
00:08:13,541 --> 00:08:14,640
Archie.

158
00:08:16,144 --> 00:08:17,577
I got you a little something.

159
00:08:17,580 --> 00:08:18,646
Thanks.

160
00:08:18,649 --> 00:08:20,513
- I didn't realize...
- Oh, no, no.

161
00:08:20,515 --> 00:08:22,882
It's all good. Just open it.

162
00:08:26,736 --> 00:08:28,788
- Ronnie, this is...
- Turn it over.

163
00:08:30,808 --> 00:08:32,241
I got it before...

164
00:08:33,891 --> 00:08:36,591
I don't want things to
be forced between us.

165
00:08:38,466 --> 00:08:39,932
What?

166
00:08:39,935 --> 00:08:41,924
No. Did I... Did I make it worse?

167
00:08:41,927 --> 00:08:44,315
I just, I wanted you to know
that I still care about...

168
00:08:44,318 --> 00:08:45,350
No, you didn't.

169
00:08:46,565 --> 00:08:48,866
Things at home aren't great right now.

170
00:08:50,211 --> 00:08:51,511
It's my dad.

171
00:08:53,148 --> 00:08:54,714
Anything I can do to help?

172
00:08:57,016 --> 00:08:58,315
Come on.

173
00:08:58,318 --> 00:08:59,786
We're still friends.

174
00:09:00,822 --> 00:09:03,222
He just, he got his
hospital bill and he owes

175
00:09:04,742 --> 00:09:06,825
$86,000, Ronnie,

176
00:09:06,828 --> 00:09:10,007
and it's like we are
selling Christmas trees,

177
00:09:10,010 --> 00:09:12,877
just for extra money so we
can keep our heads above water.

178
00:09:12,880 --> 00:09:14,261
Oh, my God, Archie.

179
00:09:15,119 --> 00:09:16,452
I want to help.

180
00:09:18,173 --> 00:09:20,606
- I want to hug you.
- That's okay.

181
00:09:21,609 --> 00:09:23,009
I shouldn't have said anything.

182
00:09:23,011 --> 00:09:24,911
The watch is great, Ronnie. Thank you.

183
00:09:24,913 --> 00:09:26,212
Yeah.

184
00:09:27,348 --> 00:09:28,781
<i>What is all this?</i>

185
00:09:28,784 --> 00:09:30,650
It's a Serpent tradition.

186
00:09:30,653 --> 00:09:33,159
Every year, we give
back to the Southside.

187
00:09:33,162 --> 00:09:34,728
Toys for Tots. Meals on Wheels,

188
00:09:34,731 --> 00:09:36,770
kids and old folks living alone.

189
00:09:36,773 --> 00:09:38,172
The Hells Angels do it.

190
00:09:38,175 --> 00:09:40,774
I'm always down for charitable works.

191
00:09:40,777 --> 00:09:42,143
Hey, have you seen my dad?

192
00:09:42,146 --> 00:09:43,346
Why aren't you in school?

193
00:09:44,135 --> 00:09:46,032
It's a half-day before break.

194
00:09:46,035 --> 00:09:48,924
Well, in that case, you can
hold down the fort here, Jug.

195
00:09:48,927 --> 00:09:51,038
Or I could come with you guys.

196
00:09:51,041 --> 00:09:53,105
Nice try. The answer's no.

197
00:09:53,108 --> 00:09:55,236
We do need another set of hands, boss.

198
00:09:55,239 --> 00:09:56,742
There you go.

199
00:09:56,745 --> 00:09:58,460
Let me pull my weight.

200
00:09:58,463 --> 00:09:59,912
Dad...

201
00:10:02,526 --> 00:10:04,566
I don't know what the Snake
Charmer has you doing...

202
00:10:04,569 --> 00:10:07,080
Sweet Pea, you're with us.

203
00:10:22,837 --> 00:10:24,070
Hey, Betty, what's up?

204
00:10:24,073 --> 00:10:27,273
Hey, I can't let this Svenson thing go.

205
00:10:27,275 --> 00:10:29,675
I think we should stop by
his house and check up on him.

206
00:10:29,678 --> 00:10:30,955
Yeah, I agree.

207
00:10:30,958 --> 00:10:32,958
Let me just tell my dad and we'll go.

208
00:10:32,961 --> 00:10:34,928
- Give me ten.
- All right.

209
00:10:36,551 --> 00:10:39,252
Teen Paul Bunyan, I'd like
to purchase your finest tree.

210
00:10:39,254 --> 00:10:41,254
Actually, Cheryl, I was
just about to take a break,

211
00:10:41,257 --> 00:10:43,130
but Vic here can help you. Vic.

212
00:10:45,719 --> 00:10:46,918
What can I get you, miss?

213
00:10:46,921 --> 00:10:48,815
We've got some nice spruces.

214
00:11:03,344 --> 00:11:05,211
Well, there's the chicken soup.

215
00:11:09,017 --> 00:11:10,516
Mr. Svenson?

216
00:11:28,269 --> 00:11:29,483
Can I help you?

217
00:11:29,486 --> 00:11:30,803
Jughead Jones?

218
00:11:32,140 --> 00:11:33,172
Maybe.

219
00:11:33,175 --> 00:11:35,748
I'm Jack Walsh, your
dad's parole officer.

220
00:11:36,277 --> 00:11:37,410
He's not home.

221
00:11:37,413 --> 00:11:38,811
Doesn't need to be.

222
00:11:38,814 --> 00:11:41,134
Do you mind if I come in for a moment?

223
00:11:41,137 --> 00:11:43,082
Like I have a choice.

224
00:11:46,854 --> 00:11:49,455
Hiram. Was that a Spiffany's bag I saw

225
00:11:49,457 --> 00:11:51,733
coming through the lobby earlier today?

226
00:11:51,736 --> 00:11:54,127
It looked about the right
size for a <i>Glamerge</i> egg.

227
00:11:54,130 --> 00:11:55,320
That depends, mi amore. Have

228
00:11:55,323 --> 00:11:56,893
